            "answer_text": "The basicity of an acid is equivalent to the number of H+ produced by an acid, when it gets ionized in the aqueous medium. So, for sulphuric acid, it is 2. One can say that the basicity of the acids is equal to the hydrogen atom present in the acid. ",
